1. Lie on the floor with your bottom about 2 to 3 feet away from an elevated platform (weight bench or edge of the sofa). Place right foot on platform edge. Fold the thigh of the left leg toward your chest, bending at the knee. 2. Lift both hips off the floor by driving your foot into the platform, bringing your heel up at the top of the movement and keeping your left knee bent. Squeeze your glutes and pause at the top for two seconds, then lower slowly. Repeat eight to 10 times on each side for two to three sets.
